					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in front of the Āñjanēya temple.</p>						

						<p>Vijayanagara: Sadāśivarāya.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1465, Śōbhakṛit, Śrāvaṇa śu. 12,</hi> corresponding to 1542 A.D., July 23, Sunday.</p>						

						<p>Slightly damaged. It records a gift of land to the temple of Hanuman probably by Rāmarāju China Timmarāju who received as <hi rend="italic">uṁbali,</hi> villages Toravēmula and Kalumaḷa in the Rāmēśvaram-Podaṭūrisima, granted to him as <hi rend="italic">nāyaṅkara.</hi></p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">Inscriptions of Andhra Pradesh: Cuddapah District,</hi> Part II, No. 160.]</p>						

						</summary>
